&lt;DIV&gt;The exploit to the mail delivery quest is since you can die and respawn with eveyrthing there's no risk in death. However the problem is people are running this quest 100's of times leaving hundreds of corpses. And since corpses even without stuff on them don't decay for a week? everything is backed up. This is cheating.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So for the developers, a two suggestions:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1.&amp;nbsp;Since hide corpse all resets (showing all corpses)&amp;nbsp;everytime you zone, &lt;U&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;is is possible to set it up in the .ini file as a default setting so show corpses are off or on? &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/U&gt;Lets say always on so you aren't having to load everyone's body when you zone?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2. Alternative, put in the old rules, &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;U&gt;you don't respawn with our gear when you die from level 1 up. You only have 30 mnutes to cr the body too.&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt; I don't think the quest should be nerf'd but I also don't think we should reward people exploiting a definite weakness in the game which their selfishness results and causing the game to be unplayable for others.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
